race.description: Ted Ryder Cup Day December 24 Maiden Plate
race.comment: BRENLYN'S LEGACY (5) showed promise on debut at Wodonga when chasing gamely into the placings back in May. Has trialled well since and possesses enough speed to overcome the tricky draw. Perfect chance to break through. DEFLECTOR (9) resumes for the local stable and while the maiden win has proven elusive, he hasn't been without merit. The booking of McDougall first-up is a key push and he can give this a big shake. GOBINDA (2) has been holding his form nicely and looks to be peaking now. Should be right in the mix. APERA (12), a Vino Rosso filly on debut for the Gorrel yard, chased strongly in her Albury trial and draws well. Market moves will be telling. SARAYA (10) struggles to convert but has produced solid Victorian efforts that measure up here. Likely to go forward and give himself every chance.
